GateDocument.TextWithNodes: System will implement Access Control List mechanism to obtain information security. ACL system will be derived from the hierarchy in hospital / healthcare environments. System will authenticate user via login and password and check which hospital, department or ward user belongs to. System will support optional SSL encryption. For every action done with a patient system will have a record in the data the user viewed / modified / created. System will implement session time outs and use cookies to terminate an electronic session. System will allow for scheduling appointments. System will store appointment's date, department, physician or clinician and purpose. System will allow for creating bills. System will allow for patient admission. System will allow for storing patient images or photos. System will allow for storing encounter images or photos. System will allow for department administration. System will implement diagnoses, procedures DRG. System will implement Duty Plan Managements for Doctors. System will implement Duty Plan Managements for Nurses. System will allow for searchin for DICOM Images. System will allow for managing Insurance Company information. System will allow for ordering non-pharmaceutical products via Medical Depot. System will manage Nurses information. System will allow for searching for nurses. System will allow for viewing ward's occupancy list. System will allow for admitting a client to a ward. System will display reports and test results. System will allow for entering intra-ward notes about a client. System will allow for discharging a client. System will allow for transfering a client. System will allow to open a client's charts folder. Charts folder will store information on temperature and blood pressure values. Chart folder will store information on diet plan. Chart folder will store information on allergy. Chart folder will store information on diagnosis and therapy notes. Chart folder will store information on daily notes. Chart folder will store information on anticoagulant prescription. Chart folder will store information on anticoagulant dosage / administration notes. Chart folder will store information on medicine prescriptions. Chart folder will store information on daily medicine dosage and administration notes. Chart folder will store information on physical therapy, anti-thrombosis-gymnastics and related notes. System will allow for personnel managemet. System will allow for registering a new doctor. System will allow for assigning a doctor to a department. System will allow for registering a new nurse. System will allow for assigning a nurse to a department. System will allow for submitting a test request to a physician or clinician. System will maintaing a telephone directory of people, departments, rooms and wards.
